pos;t adequately anticipated the ferocity of the counter-revolutionary reaction from the establishment. They were determined not to make the same mistake."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwELM">Harris, James (July 26, 2016). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://historynewsnetwork.org/article/163498" id="mwELQ">"Historian James Harris says Russian archives show we've misunderstood Stalin"</a>. <i id="mwELU"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./History_News_Network" title="History News Network" id="mwELY">History News Network</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwELc">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwELg">December 1,</span> 2018</span>. <q id="mwELk">So what was the motivation behind the Terror? The answers required a lot more digging, but it gradually became clearer that the violence of the late 1930s was driven by fear. Most Bolsheviks, Stalin among them, believed that the revolutions of 1789, 1848 and 1871 had failed because their leaders hadn't adequately anticipated the ferocity of the counter-revolutionary reaction from the establishment. They were determined not to make the same mistake.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=History+News+Network&amp;rft.atitle=Historian+James+Harris+says+Russian+archives+show+we%27ve+misunderstood+Stalin&amp;rft.date=2016-07-26&amp;rft.aulast=Harris&amp;rft.aufirst=James&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fhistorynewsnetwork.org%2Farticle%2F163498&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Stalin" class="Z3988" about="#mwt2319" id="mwELo"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt2319" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwELs"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMcDermott20065–6-875" id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEMcDermott20065–6-875"><a href="./Joseph_Stali